      <hedline>
        <hl1>B.A.T. PROFITS RISE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Alan Cowell</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>British American Tobacco PLC reports first-half pretax profits rose 6 percent, to $1.04 billion, as its global sales increased 23 percent, to 396 billion cigarettes (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>British American Tobacco P.L.C., manufacturer of brands that include Lucky Strike, Kent, Dunhill and Rothmans, said first-half pretax profits rose 6 percent, to $1.04 billion, as its global sales increased 23 percent, to 396 billion cigarettes.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell (NYT)</p>
      </block>
